laboratory_examinations.findings: In the right lower quadrant, there is a dilated tubular structure arising from the cecum measuring up to 12 mm with surrounding fat stranding and wall hyperemia, consistent with an inflamed appendix. No intra-abdominal free air or fluid collection. Limited views of the liver, spleen, pancreas, and kidneys are unremarkable. Normal caliber of small and large bowel without wall thickening.
